ACT:
 Constitution of India Article 226-Maintainability of writ petition at the stage of show cause notice to terminate the services of a service personnel by the Chief of the Army staff when the finding of a court martial even on revision is perverse or against the weight of evidence on record-Army Act, 1950 sections 18 to 24, 108, 121, 127, 153, 154, 160(1), 191 and the Army Rules 1954 Rules 14 and 68 to 71, scope of-Competency of the Chief of the Army Staff to have recourse to Rule 14 of the Army Rules, when the general court martial originally and on revision returned a verdict of "Not guilty" -Principle of double jeopardy Aufrefois Acquit applicability-Constitution of India Article 20(2) read with Army Act, section 121.
 
